{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkingInVsCode"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Visual Studio Code provides a compelling alternative to Xcode for SwiftGodot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"developers on Mac, Linux, or Windows."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Prerequisites","level":3,"anchor":"Prerequisites"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To develop with SwiftGodot in Visual Studio Code, you will need the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prerequisites:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Godot Engine without .NET support from the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/godotengine.org\/download\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Studio Code from the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/Download","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Swift from the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Configuring Visual Studio Code","level":3,"anchor":"Configuring-Visual-Studio-Code","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Swift Extension for Visual Studio Code from the Swift Server Work Group"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"provides code completion, code navigation, build task creation, and integration"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with LLDB for debugging, along with many other features for devloping code with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install the Swift Extension for Visual Studio from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/marketplace.visualstudio.com\/items?itemName=sswg.swift-lang","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or search for Swift on the Extensions tab in Visual Studio Code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Installing the Swift Extension will automatically install the CodeLLDB Extension","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as a dependency for Visual Studio Code for debugging support."}]},{"text":"Create a Swift library package for your project","anchor":"Create-a-Swift-library-package-for-your-project","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a folder on disk in a file location near the Godot project that you want"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to use with SwiftGodot.  For this article, we will assume you are working"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"against the sample project and code from the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/tutorials\/swiftgodot-tutorials"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On the commmand line, change directories into the folder you created and run the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"swift package command to initialize a new library package:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"swift package init --type library","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can now open your package folder in Visual Studio Code:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"code .","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or use the “Open Folder…” File menu option in Visual Studio Code."}]},{"text":"Setup SwiftGodot in Package.swift","type":"heading","anchor":"Setup-SwiftGodot-in-Packageswift","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inside Visual Studio Code, open Package.swift","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the minimum platform target to macOS 13 and set your library type to dynamic by adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"type: .dynamic,","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to the products library section of your package configuration. E.g.,","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["platforms: [.macOS(.v13)],","products: [","   .library(","      name: \"SimpleRunnerDriver\",","      type: .dynamic,","      targets: [\"SimpleRunnerDriver\"]),","]"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the SwiftGodot dependency to your package.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["dependencies: [","   .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/migueldeicaza\/SwiftGodot\", branch: \"main\")","],"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Modify your library target to reference the SwitGodot dependency, and add"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"necessary swift compiler and linker settings:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".target(","   name: \"SimpleRunnerDriver\",","   dependencies: [","         \"SwiftGodot\",","   ],","   swiftSettings: [.unsafeFlags([\"-suppress-warnings\"])]","),"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At this point, you should be able to follow the Meet SwiftGodot Tutorial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"beginning in Section 2."}]},{"text":"Building your SwiftGodot package","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Building-your-SwiftGodot-package"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you are ready to build your SwiftGodot package, the Swift Extension"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provides a default Build task you can execute with Visual Studio Code’s Build"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Shortcut - Ctrl+Shift+B (or Cmd+Shift+B on Mac)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The initial build, especially on Windows, may take a very long time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Setting-up-your-gdextension","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Setting up your gdextension"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When creating your "},{"code":"gdextension","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file, your configuration file will need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contain settings specific to your platform, and you will need to copy the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"libraries for your operating system and architecture to the "},{"code":"bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" folder inside","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"your Godot project.","type":"text"}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Windows","text":"Windows"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Windows does not deal well with long paths, so you should make sure that you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"either checkout your SwiftGodot into a toplevel directory, or use the Windows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"subst","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" command to map a drive name to the location that contains your","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot builds."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are developing on Windows, your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libraries"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dependencies","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will need"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to be specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"windows.debug.x86_64"},{"text":" and your libraries will be compiled","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dll"},{"text":" files, so that these sections should look like this:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["[libraries]","windows.debug.x86_64 = \"res:\/\/bin\/SimpleRunnerDriver.dll\"","","[dependencies]","windows.debug.x86_64 = {\"res:\/\/bin\/SwiftGodot.dll\" : \"\"}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can copy these files to your Godot projects ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bin"},{"type":"text","text":" folder from the build"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"output folder located in ","type":"text"},{"code":".build\\x86_64-unknown-windows-msvc\\debug\\","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" inside","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the directory where you initialized your Swift package."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an additional step on Windows, you will need to copy all of the Swift"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"runtime libraries into the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bin"},{"type":"text","text":" folder with SwiftGodot.dll.  This is means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"copying all ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"*.dll"},{"text":" files from ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\Program Files\\Swift\\runtime-development\\usr\\bin\\","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Linux","text":"Linux"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you are developing on Linux, your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libraries"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dependencies","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to be specified as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"linux.debug.x86_64"},{"text":" and your libraries will be compiled into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"lib*.so","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" files, so that these sections should look like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["[libraries]","linux.debug.x86_64 = \"res:\/\/bin\/libSimpleRunnerDriver.so\"","","[dependencies]","linux.debug.x86_64 = {\"res:\/\/bin\/libSwiftGodot.so\" : \"\"}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can copy these files to your Godot projects "},{"code":"bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" folder from the build"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"output folder located in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".build\/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\/debug\/"},{"type":"text","text":" inside"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the directory where you initialized your Swift package."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Debugging-your-SwiftGodot-code","text":"Debugging your SwiftGodot code"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can debug your SwiftGodot code on Windows or Linux using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"CodeLLDB Extension to launch your game directly from vscode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to do this, you will need to add a Launch"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"task to your project.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In Visual Sutdio Code, switch to the “Run and Debug” tab.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"code":"launch.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file by tapping on “create a launch.json file”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and selecting “LLDB”, which should be the first suggested option."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the newly created launch.json file, you should modify the existing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lldb task to support launching as follows:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Change the value for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Launch Godot Game"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a line for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"program"},{"type":"text","text":" with the path to your Godot executable"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a line for "},{"code":"args","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with any necessary arguments to launch your game,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as the path to your godot project","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"specify the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cwd"},{"text":" (current working directory)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your launch configuration for lldb should now look like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"json","code":["{","   \"type\": \"lldb\",","   \"request\": \"launch\",","   \"name\": \"Launch Godot Game\",","   \"program\": \"path\/to\/your\/Godot\/executable\",","   \"args\": [\"--path\", \"path\/to\/your\/game\/project\"],","   \"cwd\": \"${workspaceFolder}\"","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you save this file, “Launch Godot Game” will appear as the default debug","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"task in the “Run and Debug” sidebar.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"To run this task, click on the green play button next to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“Launch Godot Game” in the “Run and Debug” sidebar."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This action will launch the game with the LLDB debugger attached."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this point, Visual Studio Code should now stop on any breakpoints you have","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set, and you should be able to inspect Variables, set Watches, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"(Optional) Add a `Attach` Debug task","anchor":"Optional-Add-a-Attach-Debug-task","level":4},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open the launch.json file."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a comma after the last closing brace ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"}"},{"type":"text","text":" of the existing configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Paste the following configuration:","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"type\": \"lldb\",","    \"request\": \"attach\",","    \"name\": \"Attach to PID\",","    \"pid\": \"${command:pickProcess}\"","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Your ","type":"text"},{"code":"launch.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" should now look something like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"json","code":["{","   \"version\": \"0.2.0\",","   \"configurations\": [","      {","         \"type\": \"lldb\",","         \"request\": \"launch\",","         \"name\": \"Launch Godot Game\",","         \"program\": \"path\/to\/your\/Godot\/executable\",","         \"args\": [\"--path\", \"path\/to\/your\/game\/project\"],","         \"cwd\": \"${workspaceFolder}\"","      },","      {","         \"type\": \"lldb\",","         \"request\": \"attach\",","         \"name\": \"Attach to PID\",","         \"pid\": \"${command:pickProcess}\"","      }","   ]","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you save this file, “Attach to PID” should appear in the debug options list."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To debug your app using “Attach to PID”, follow these steps:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"First, take note of running Godot process PIDs by running “Attach to PID”","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and searching for Godot."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Launch your game from Godot"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Return to Visual Studio and press F5 to run “Attach to PID” again."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Search again for Godot and select the PID for your game, which should be the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only process that wasn’t listed in step (1) above."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Linux or Mac, it may be possible to differentiate your game’s PID from other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Godot PIDs by looking at the additional information Visual Studio Code lists about"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"each process, including command line options.  On Windows, the Godot processes are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"pretty much identical, making it difficult to differentiate your game from the editor."}]}]},{"name":"Warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"On Mac, you will need to make your Godot engine debuggable following the steps from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this article ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/debuginxcode","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],"style":"warning"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"iden